verbose_text: In contrast, significantly lower levels of IL-1beta and IL-8 were secreted by PMNs from diabetic patients (XREF_FIG; P < 0.001) and observed over a range of 0.3-10 multiplicity of infection (MOI) (XREF_FIG; P < 0.05), indicating that this phenotype is unlikely to result from reduced contact between PMNs of diabetic subjects and the bacteria.
